rComments: She is the antithesis of ECON 202'S Colleen Schulz in so many ways it is actually quite amusing. She is very enthusiastic about her subject and her work, genuinely interested in answering questions and helping you out in any way possible, and has none of the attitude problems that unfortunately afflicts  Schultz. Very much recommended!

She is extremely helpful and available at all times.  Her test is very fair but you must attend to her classes If you study the lecture and in class notes and skim through the book you will receive A- if you want to do really good on the exams please do attend to her review sessions.   I hope you are the lucky one to take her class

She's nice, but her class is boring & difficult to follow. She can't really teach well, & the exams are horrible.  I got sick & my midterm weight was shifted to my final for 80% of my total grade. If you're not great at calc expect a horrible flaming death. The exam questions build off each other so if you screw up a part you're F*cked!

Zaruhi is definitely the professor to have for ECON 302.  I had Arvin-Rad and dropped.. Zaruhi was much easier.  She is very helpful with homework.  As the person below me said, go to class for her examples because they are on  hw and the exams.  Definitely easier than other 302 professors!!

If you can take her for 302, do it! From what I've heard from people in other 302 classes, she definitely made this class a lot easier. Midterm and final counted for 80% of the grade but were pretty easy and she let us know what to study in the reviews. Shes a bad lecturer, but go to class to copy down her examples...identical to hw and tests

Nice lady, bad teacher. Her section wasn't too difficult as far as ECON 302 goes (I've heard it can be brutal). Final exam was 50% of the grade, and she didn't give much clue as to what would be on it. Midterm and final were bother very short, so if you missed a few questions it had a substantial impact your final grade.
Class followed the book note by note, homework and tests were based off her examples and the book examples.  She's a nice lady.

Even though she clearly knows her stuff, she is awful at imparting her knowledge upon her students. Most of this class you will need to learn on your own because all she does is download the power point slides from the book author's website and talk through them. She is a terrible lecturer.
easiest class ever don't have to go to discussion, hw is easy just do your work and you'll do good in the class
she does her job. can't complain. she's a funny character with her weird comments. if you need help and ask, she'll definitely try to help.
Great TA, just loved her. Cares a lot about a student.
